1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on wireless communication and scheduling in a UAV-enabled network, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper involves the use of a UAV as a mobile base station, which can be considered a robotic application. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with optimizing the communication throughput, which is a fundamental problem in information theory. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper involves trajectory optimization for a UAV, which can be considered a control problem. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The proposed algorithm for solving the optimization problem involves iterative techniques, which can be considered a form of artificial intelligence.
